{
  "texts": [
    "This corresponds to the 2-charge in which there is no interaction between the induced and localized symmetries.2.",
    "Choose the \"electric\" line e as the generator of the 2 1-form symmetry.",
    "This corresponds to the 2-charge in which the induced symmetry is charged under localized symmetry.3.",
    "Choose the \"magnetic\" line m as the generator of the 2 1-form symmetry.",
    "This corresponds to the 2-charge in which the induced symmetry sources the localized symmetry.Note that we cannot choose the \"dyonic\"/\"fermionic\" line ψ as the generator of 2 1form symmetry, because the ψ line is a fermion (recall θ (ψ) = -1) and hence generates a 2 1-form symmetry with a non-trivial 't Hooft anomaly."
  ]
}